Description: XSDM is a tool that integrates concepts of 
    stochastic demography into species distribution modelling.
    Inferences, utilizing Bayesian methods based in Stan,
    are made of aspects of the environmental niche of a species,
    and those inferences can be used to project species
    geographic range. Data requirements include species
    detection records and spatiotemporal environmental data.
    See <doi:10.1101/2024.10.30.621023> for a description of
    the statistical and demographic models used.
URL: <doi:10.1101/2024.10.30.621023>
